              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31459172-chafic-rello?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31459172-chafic-rello?shelf=world-lebanon">world-lebanon</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1034319480" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9605048158208628130">This book is older than I am.<br/>But, I had read it while I was in Lebanon - and while dated, time hasn&apos;t changed the underlying commentary in the book.<br/><br/>What would normally spark quite a heated debate is broken down and approached from a historical/empirical view of the matter that highlights the different dynamics of both Lebanon and Israel.<br/><br/>It&apos;s well-written, it&apos;s informative and got my 24-year old adolescent brain actually thinking about a topic I&apos;ve been oblivious to.<br/></span>
